      "text": "call InnerWithFailingRecovery, on error set %outerCaught% = true",
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "indent": 0,
      "comment": "When the recovery body itself throws, error.handle.Wrap leaves Handled=false on the inner Call and re-throws \u2014 the original error propagates (with the recovery error chained) and the outer handler catches it. Side-effect proof: %outerCaught% gets set by the outer handler, which only fires if the inner recovery failed and re-threw.",
